{
  "text": "A somewhat related question was discuss in [CITATION_1] where efficient deterministic constructions for combinatorial hitting sets are given. A hitting set for a domain {1, . . . , m} d guarantees to \"hit\" any combinatorial rectangle of volume at least , i.e., any combinatorial rectangle that includes at least m d points would intersect the hitting set in at least one point. The main contribution of [CITATION_2] is to construct such a hitting set deterministically (i.e., without any randomization) and have its size and computation time be polynomial in m, d and 1/ .",
